## Set up OS
Start with Fedora 37. Run all updates.
sudo dnf group install "C Development Tools and Libraries" "Development Tools"

## Clone ChromeOS kernel
git clone https://github.com/eupnea-linux/chromeos-kernel
edit kernel_versions.json and replace "chromeos-5.10": "release-R110-15278.B-chromeos-5.10", with "chromeos-5.10": "release-R108-15183.B-chromeos-5.10"

## Build it (this will take 30-40 mins depending on your CPU)
python kernel_build.py -i chromeos-5.10

## Copy files
bzImage-stable or whatever the name is needs to go into /boot/vmlinuz-5.10.147
install modules with tar xf modules-stable.tar.xz -C /lib/modules

## After build, install
sudo dracut --kver 5.10.147 initramfs-5.10.147.img
sudo chmod +x /boot/vmlinuz-5.10.147

## Update grub
sudo grub2-mkconfig -o /boot/efi/EFI/fedora/grub.cfg
